PAULDING WIND FARM IV LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Paulding Wind Farm IV LLC ("Paulding IV") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Paulding IV generating facility ("Paulding IV Facility").
The Paulding IV Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Paulding County, Ohio. The Paulding IV Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by AEP Ohio Transmission Company, Inc. and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Paulding IV's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Paulding IV Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Paulding IV's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Paulding IV shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $450,000.00 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $37,500.00
